    {
      "id": "68",
      "name": "Lore",
      "components": [
        {
          "component_id": "customize",
          "data": {
            "data": {
              "parsed_content": [
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Vennessa",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 1,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/02/21/237301566/838b9700660c599eb0035c31c730636e_7477418653650690401.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Vennessa and her clan were originally from Natlan and were the \"children\" of the Goddess of War, who was at that time the Pyro Archon. The children of the Lady of Fire were strong and proud people who lived on the slopes of volcanoes far to the west. All of them were blessed with fiery red hair. Many years ago, they left Natlan and wandered in the sea of grass, trying to survive. Ten years before Vennessa met Venti, Vennessa's clan encountered Ursa the Drake, who had terrorized Mondstadt for many years. Fleeing from Ursa after starving for four days, the Natlanese ended up in Mondstadt, where aristocrats ruled at the time.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "When Decarabian, the previous ruler of Mondstadt, was overthrown, the God of Wind, Barbatos, took over Mondstadt. He taught people freedom, festivals, and flights and left the rule of the nobility, falling into sleep. At first, aristocrats were an example for people, but over time, power corrupted them. They brought back slavery and gladiator fights for their entertainment, and one of the main festivals, Ludi Harpastum, was turned from a celebration for the people into a celebration for the dominant Lawrence clan. One of the traditions of the festival was to choose a girl who would throw the red ball called Harpastum into the crowd. It was believed that the first person to touch the ball would have good luck all year. But the Lawrences forbade ordinary people to touch the ball, and the girl chosen to be the Princess of Ludi Harpastum was personally taken by the lordling Barca Lawrence.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "right",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/02/21/237301566/077320c3e1d06a4f9533ac5fda2f61e2_6810935349219545549.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "When Vennessa's clan came to Mondstadt, the lords enslaved them, and Vennessa was made a gladiator. They promised her that after twelve battles, they would grant freedom to her and her people, so she fought fiercely for them. One day she prayed to Celestia and asked the gods for help and the salvation of her clan. The Anemo Archon, Barbatos, awoke from his sleep after hearing her prayers and descended into Mondstadt under the guise of a simple bard, Venti.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Venti came to Ludi Harpastum and saw what the nobles had turned the festival into. Ludi Harpastum was a festival that Anemo Archon created to teach the people of his country freedom, joy, and winemaking. The God of Freedom did not agree to obey the lords, so he picked Harpastum, provoking the wrath of Barca Lawrence, who ordered the guards to capture the bard. Venti, running away from the guards, ran into Vennessa, who was buying herbs for a sick girl from her clan. Lawrence ordered Vennessa to move away to capture Venti, but she refused, protecting the bard. To take revenge on Vennessa, Barca asked his father to ransom Vennessa's entire clan, and he locked Vennessa behind bars to send her to the final battle the next day.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "At night, Venti made his way to Vennessa, thanking her for the protection, inviting her to become friends, and telling her about Murata. The bard was sorry to see her shackles, so he suggested she flee, but Vennessa refused, as she needed to protect her people from Barca's wrath.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/02/21/237301566/db0d6bb57e72161786db2b32170f79fd_1400062299052685947.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Vennessa's last opponent was supposed to be Ursa the Drake, but Lawrence sent not only her but her entire clan, including children and old people, to fight. Lord Lawrence, in case of victory, promised to free all slaves and give Vennessa his wealth and the key to Mondstadt. Ursa and his minions were waiting in front of the Muratans, and behind them, the archers of the aristocrats did not allow the slaves to retreat into the city. Just when Vennessa thought they would all die, Venti appeared, revealing his divine form. He endowed Vennessa's sword with the power of the wind and helped drive away the dragon.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "After the victory over Ursa, Venti demanded the promised freedom, riches, and keys to the city from the Lawrences. Vennessa, with the help of Ragnvindr, the Dawn Knight, a former member of the Lawrence family Kreuzlied, and other disgruntled people, began a rebellion against the Aristocracy, overthrowing all the lords and returning power to the people.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Related Entries:",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 3796,
                      "icon_url": "https://upload-static.hoyoverse.com/hoyolab-wiki/2023/04/26/237301566/a19531bd8e93b793b79bfe1499b5b5d7_7637529122280724157.png",
                      "name": "Мондштадт",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 4809,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/08/31/237301566/8694aaf89d32e75eca416ec7fe41e487_8636855791292057309.png",
                      "menu_id": 22,
                      "name": "Natlan",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 7468,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2025/02/25/237301566/5f7d70114271f8eca21f24cd62499dc6_6114532498612516105.png",
                      "menu_id": 10,
                      "name": "Barbatos",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 2033,
                      "icon_url": "https://bbs.hoyolab.com/hoyowiki/picture/weapon/钟剑.png",
                      "name": "Меч-колокол",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 2075,
                      "icon_url": "https://bbs.hoyolab.com/hoyowiki/picture/reliquary/Noblesse Oblige/flower_of_life_icon.png",
                      "name": "Церемония древней знати",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 2297,
                      "icon_url": "https://bbs.hoyolab.com/hoyowiki/picture/book/Ballads of the Squire_icon.png",
                      "name": "Баллады оруженосца",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Knights of Favonius",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 1,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/02/21/237301566/abd8efbb6bea59bcf72a9d3b0e73a118_5177554025741331531.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "After defeating the aristocrats, Vennessa founded the Knights of Favonius, an order of knights ruling over Mondstadt, and became the first Grand Master and the Dandelion Knight. During her reign, four defenders called the Four Winds were summoned to protect Mondstadt: the Wolf of the North, Andrius, who once fought the tyrant Decarabian; the Falcon of the West, Vennessa; the Dragon of the East, Dvalin, a friend of Barbatos; and the Lion of the South — the Dandelion Knight (currently Jean). For many years, the people of Mondstadt worshiped the guardians to whom they built temples, but after the Cataclysm that occurred 500 years ago, the temples were abandoned, and the Four Winds were forgotten.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/02/21/237301566/40aabcd7e8b3d68d92a61d92ec42daad_8307353104923142834.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Years later, after the restoration of Mondstadt, Vennessa ascended to Celestia in the form of a falcon. She's still keeping watch over Mondstadt after all these years.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "In the place where she ascended, a giant oak grew. The shade of the tree protects the Statue of The Seven built at its feet from the rain and the wind,",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "alignment": "right",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/02/21/237301566/fb58ef9b392d7563bd1f8d09c8efe065_3411328579290626231.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "like Vennessa once protected Mondstadt. This oak has a special connection to the Anemo element and to the Anemo Archon himself. When Barbatos was injured after losing his Gnosis, he was able to heal near the Symbol of Mondstadt's Hero.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "As Venti promised, she forever remained the heroine of Mondstadt, about whom songs were written.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"When days become nights and faces fill with despair,",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "Never forget the heroic tales of Vennessa, the dame with the flaming hair!",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "Never cease to pursue freedom, even when the land is bare!\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Related Entries:",
                      "type": "text"
