    {
      "id": "93",
      "name": "Mentions",
      "components": [
        {
          "component_id": "customize",
          "data": {
            "data": {
              "parsed_content": [
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 23,
                      "icon_url": "https://bbs.hoyolab.com/hoyowiki/picture/character/Venti_icon.png",
                      "name": "Venti",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold"
                      ],
                      "text": "Character Story",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 3,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Character Story 2",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "There is a towering oak tree at the center of Windrise, said to have sprouted when Vennessa ascended to the heavens a millennium ago.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "In the past few months, travelers resting in the shade of the great oak sometimes hear a young boy singing the tales of Barbatos, the Anemo Archon.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Unlike the ruling deities of the other nations, Barbatos has long left Mondstadt. In fact, the only visible proof of his connection with Mondstadt is the Statues of The Seven that appear across the land — even then, the resemblance is vague at best. Fortunately, Barbatos's past deeds are recorded in books and epics, sung and passed on by the bards.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "In contrast to these more canonical works, Venti's ballads tend to include bizarre adventures and acts of mischief, such as the time that Barbatos pinched the Cryo Archon's scepter and replaced it with a hilichurl's wooden club...",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Worshippers of Barbatos are quick to decry these frivolous tales as blasphemous fabrications. But whenever someone confronts Venti about this, his response suggests that he has not an ounce of remorse.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "\"How can you know that they're fabrications?\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "He has a point — even the most devoted sister could not possibly know the details of all of Barbatos's deeds from a millennium ago.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Only Venti knows the truth behind his song lyrics, and it is a truth he hides behind an enigmatic smile.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Reason being, yes — Venti's tall tales of Barbatos's unorthodox exploits are entirely fabricated.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Hey, Venti finds that a few drinks really gets his muse going. Can you really blame him?",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Where the Wind Doth Not Blow",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "After 1,600 years of history, Mondstadt's \"freedom\" had sunk to a heretofore unseen low.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Barbatos, unwilling to become a tyrant, had departed. But he had never imagined that those to whom he had gifted freedom would make for themselves a tyrant.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "The aristocracy ruled Mondstadt with a cruel hand, bringing slaves into this land and ignoring the cries of the oppressed.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Thus the Anemo Archon returned after these 1,600 years to what was once the City of Freedom. He heard the cry of the slave girl Vennessa, and together with her raised a rebellion that overthrew the aristocracy.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "—Now, the above is what all know to be the official history of Mondstadt.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "The story has an interesting, little-known twist, however.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "The one who united the people of Mondstadt in this conflict was indeed the hero Vennessa — but that which caused many of the aristocracy's troops to turn coat was a \"treachery against the wind.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "A secret treaty was found, a betrayal of the city — the aristocrats had forsaken the wind, and sold everything in Mondstadt to the Geo Archon of the neighboring land.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "At the treaty's end was carved an insignia inimitable by all save the deity so named: Rex Lapis.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "How the soldiers that had once oppressed the slaves shuddered when they saw that they too would become slaves in a foreign land.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "The news, and the conflict, spread like wildfire, consuming the aristocracy. It was only many years later that historians would discover that this treaty was fake.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "As it turned out, Venti had once practiced the art of forgery in order to play pranks on the Geo Archon, but could never deceive the god of wealth and transactions. Even so, his adeptness would come into play after several hundred years.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "What a happy coincidence.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 27,
                      "icon_url": "https://bbs.hoyolab.com/hoyowiki/picture/character/Jean_icon.png",
                      "name": "Jean",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold"
                      ],
                      "text": "Character Story",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 3,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Character Story 4",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "The great tree at Windrise is where the first Dandelion Knight came to the end of her journey.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "She was Vennessa, the founder of the Knights of Favonius and the restorer of Mondstadt.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "She bade farewell to the city she had vowed to protect, leaving behind her legend and a single sapling.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "After centuries of basking in the bliss of the thousand winds, this sapling grew into a towering tree.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Jean was conferred the title of \"Dandelion Knight\" at the age of fifteen.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "The Dandelion Knight is also known as Lionfang Knight. Passed down through generations of knights, the title is bestowed upon only the most distinguished.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "On the day she received the title, Jean excused herself from the celebrations that followed the conferment ceremony. As if following in the footsteps of her childhood hero, she went and stood before the great tree.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "The title of Dandelion Knight symbolizes Vennessa's legacy of resistance and benevolence. So how, Jean thought, could one such as herself be worthy of this honorable title?",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "More than a millennium had passed since Mondstadt's restoration. Did she really have what it would take to continue to protect this ancient and proud land of freedom?",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Beneath her outwardly mature visage lay the heart of a young girl, who had only just received the title and remained wholly unprepared for the task that lay before her.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "The wind blew from far away, and she felt it flow within her as it gently whisked away her doubts and worries, leaving her with an unwavering determination:",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "For Mondstadt, as always.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "To become a warrior as kind and as determined as Vennessa, and to fight for her people and for freedom... Yes, this was the true meaning of her simple family motto.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "To this day, whenever Jean feels weary or feels herself beginning to waver, she comes and stands before this tree and lets the wind console her once more. It carries away her fatigue, so that she may once more have the strength to carry on.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "The great tree at Windrise marked the end of the first Lionfang Knight's journey.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "So too does it symbolize the beginning of Jean's.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Voice-Overs",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 3,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "More About Jean: II",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Vennessa's title — \"Dandelion Knight\" — has been passed down from generation to generation. Countless great knights were awarded with this honor and I will not bring shame to this name. Thus, I must keep going. I must become the sword and aegis of the people.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
